1.	The parade forms on the outbound side of North St. at Faneuil Hall, then steps off from North St. onto Congress St. to Court St. to 138 Tremont St. to the Cathedral Church of St. Paul NLT 1:00PM for the traditional Church Service.
2.	Following the Church Service, the parade reforms at 1:45 PM on Tremont St. The parade will proceed along Tremont St., turn right onto Boylston St. proceed to Charles St. turn right onto the Charles St. Walkway to the Boston Common Parade Ground NLT 2:15 PM for the Drum Head Election and the Change-of-Command Ceremony.
3.	Governor Baker officiates at the Change-of-Command Ceremony at 2:45 PM.
4.	At the conclusion of the ceremony (3:45 PM) the parade follows the Common walkways to the intersection of Boylston and Charles Streets then crosses Boylston St. and enters Charles St. to St. James St. to Huntington Ave. terminating at the Marriott Copley Place Hotel.

The race begins at the Law School on the Boston University campus. The school’s address is 765 Commonwealth Avenue, however the building itself is actually set back from Commonwealth Avenue behind other buildings. Our formation point for the race is behind Marsh Chapel on Bay State Road. The section of the road where the race begins is rarely used on the weekend and is not a public thruway. 
The race starts at 10:00am and runners head east on Bay State Road. The roadway between the formation point and Granby Street is rarely used on the weekend.  We utilize a BUPD and BPD police detail to limit traffic for the one-block area of Bay State Road between Granby Street and Silber Way, where very limited street traffic may occur.  The runners then turn left onto Silber Way (Sherborn St.) and over the footbridge crossing Storrow Drive onto the Esplanade. Runners continue in the same eastward direction on the Esplanade until they reach the first inlet of the Charles River Reservation. At this point the runners turn around and head back in the same direction from which they came, finishing the race at the School of Law.  Our race typically has around 250 participants.

At Day Boulevard, the race will go to the right of Farragut Statue, cross Day Boulevard and go up onto the sidewalk, veering left and continuing (on the) sidewalk along Day Boulevard towards Castle Island.  The race will stay on the perimeter sidewalk of the Castle Island Parking Lot.

Before reaching Sullivan’s Restaurant, the race course will keep right (keeping Sullivan’s on the left and the Castle on the right) and circle the Castle.  Halfway around the Castle after the Korean War Memorial, the race will bear left and proceed onto the walkway around the Sugar Bowl.  The race will stay to the right of the Lighthouse.  

At the end of the walkway, the runners will go right, staying on the sidewalk until the race reaches the end of Farragut Park and goes left on Shore Drive (aka Lovers Lane).  Continuing around Farragut Park, taking a left on Farragut Road, the runners will then turn right onto East Broadway, finishing at O Street and East Broadway.

Columbus Ave is 54' wide. From the curb at the Park Plaza to the white stripe is 34'. From the white stripe to the curb at Statler Park is 20'. There is parking along the curb at Statler Park. From light pole to light pole on the Park Plaza side is 120'. On the right side of the light pole is the loading dock, on the left side is the valet station.  The valets stack cars between the light poles. 
We request suspending  public parking on the Statler Park side (9 spaces), and allow the valets to stack cars there. We would block off a 34' x 120' section from light pole to light pole and curb to white stripe with tall cones and connectors or plastic barricades and cover the area with a tent. 
Setup would take place from midnight to 6:00 am. Tear down from 4:30 pm - 10:00 pm. A police detail would be in place at all times.  
This proposal would not impact either pedestrian or motor vehicle traffic, the loading dock or the valets

The Race will Start at O Street and East Broadway Street down East Broadway towards Pleasure Bay. At Day Boulevard there will be course marshals directing runners, as the race will go to the right of Farragut Statue, cross Day Boulevard and go up onto the sidewalk, veering left and continuing (on the) sidewalk along Day Boulevard towards Castle Island.  The race will stay on the perimeter sidewalk of the Castle Island Parking Lot.  Course marshals will be directing runners around the parking lot.

After passing around the parking lot, the race continues through a non traffic pathway

Before reaching Sullivan’s Restaurant, the race course will keep right (keeping Sullivan’s on the left and the Castle on the right) and circle the Castle.  Halfway around the Castle after the Korean War Memorial, the race will bear left and proceed onto the walkway around the Sugar Bowl.  The race will stay to the right of the Lighthouse.  

At the end of the walkway, (non traffic pathway ends) the runners will go right, staying on the sidewalk until the race reaches the end of Farragut Park and goes left on Shore Drive (aka Lovers Lane).  State Police and Course Marshals will be directing traffic runners as they cross the street.  Continuing around Farragut Park, taking a left on Farragut Road. The runners will then turn right onto East Broadway, finishing at O Street and East Broadway.

This event is called "The Way of the Cross for Life".  The exact route is as follows: We will begin in front of the Most Holy Redeemer Church at 72 Maverick Street. We will proceed to Sumner Street and follow it up to the Our Lady of the Assumption Church. Then we will proceed down Lamson Street to Maverick Street and follow it to Chelsea Street. We will continue up Chelsea Street to Brooks Street and then to Paris Street where we will stop at Sacred Heart Church. Then we will proceed down to Bennington Street and follow it up to Saratoga Street, Breed Street, and Ashley Street and to St. Joseph St. Lazarus Church. Then we will go back to Bennington Street and follow it up to Walley Street and finally up Orient Avenue where we will continue to the Madonna Queen National Shrine. This will conclude our procession.

The procession begins in front of Most Holy Redeemer Church at 72 Maverick Street. It immediately turns right onto London Street and follows until it reaches Decatur Street. It then turns left onto Decatur Street and follows until it reaches Liverpool Street. It then turns left onto Liverpool Street and follows until it reaches Sumner Street. It then turns left onto Sumner Street and follows until it reaches Paris Street. It turns left onto Paris Street and follows until it reaches Meridian Street. It then turns left onto Meridian Street and follows until it reaches London Street. It then turns left onto London Street and follows to Maverick Street where it turns left to conclude in front of the church at 72 Maverick Street.

App Name: AVON 39 The Walk to End Breast
Location Description:
Note: Turn-by-turn cues will be shared at the special events meeting. 
The two-day event is scheduled to take place in Boston on July 9 and 10 starting near UMass Boston and ending Day 1 in Canton at the Reebok World Headquarters. The Day 2 route will begin at the Reebok World Headquarters and end back at UMass Boston. The route showcases the incredible Boston community. Additionally, the event provides water stops every 2-3 miles along the route with water, Gatorade, first-aid and medical support from MGH, and pre-packaged snacks. This walk takes place on sidewalks and does not request any street closures. Participants are instructed to follow regular pedestrian rules and regulations and staff travel along the route to ensure walkers are safe.
Day 1 – The route begins near UMass Boston and follows along the Harborwalk through South Boston. From there the route heads toward the Waterfront, through the Greenway and the North End to end up on Commercial Street. The route passes by TD Garden and through Beacon Hill, Boston Common, Public Gardens and the Commonwealth Mall. From there the route passes by Fenway and connects with the Emerald Necklace. Walkers pass by Harvard Medical School and down Huntington Ave and re-connect with the Emerald Necklace passing by Jamaica Pond. Walker then head to Brookline for lunch and then back down Centre Street and Washington Street in West Roxbury. Next the route will head through Dedham, Milton and Canton to end at the Reebok World Headquarters in Canton. 
Day 2 – The route starts at the Reebok World Headquarters and walkers head through Milton. From there they will connect with the Neponset Valley Trail. They will follow the trail until it ends in Dorchester. From there participants will continue north to end the day near UMass Boston.

The race starts at 10:00 am and runners head east on Bay State Road. The roadway between the formation point and Granby Street is rarely used on the weekend.  We utilize a BUPD and BPD police detail to limit traffic for the one-block area of Bay State Road between Granby Street and Silber Way, where very limited street traffic may occur.  The runners then turn left onto Silber Way (Sherborn St.) and over the footbridge crossing Storrow Drive onto the Esplanade. Runners continue in the same eastward direction on the Esplanade until they reach the first inlet of the Charles River Reservation. At this point the runners turn around and head back in the same direction from which they came, finishing the race at the School of Law.  Our race typically has around 200 participants.

The route begins at 72 Maverick Street (in front of Most Holy Redeemer Church). The route turns left onto Havre Street for one block and then turns left onto Decatur Street. The route follows two blocks until it reaches Liverpool Street where it then turns left again. It follows down Liverpool Street until it reaches Sumner Street where it then turns left again. The route follows down Sumner Street until it reaches Maverick Square at which point it turns left again. The route continues through the square until it reaches Maverick Street. At this point it turns left again and continues down Maverick Street until it reaches the church where it began. This concludes the procession.

It follows down Liverpool Street until it reaches Sumner Street where it then turns left again. The route follows down Sumner Street until it reaches Maverick Square at which point it turns left again. The route continues through the square until it reaches Maverick Street. At this point it turns left again and continues down Maverick Street until it reaches the church where it began. This concludes the procession.

The walk route will start on Charles St, take a left onto Beacon St, another left onto Arlington St, a right onto Comm Ave, and a right onto Mass Ave., where walkers will cross the Mass Ave bridge into Cambridge and then take a left onto the bike path along Memorial Drive. Walkers will follow this out to the Eliot Bridge, where they will make their way back towards Boston, again utilizing the bike path. Upon reaching the Mass Ave bridge again, walkers will go up the ramp and proceed into Mass Ave, then take a left onto Comm Ave and finish the walk on the Comm Ave mall, proceeding straight through the Boston Public Garden and into the Boston Common to finish.

The exact route is as follows: We begin in front of the Most Holy Redeemer Church at 72 Maverick Street. We will proceed to Sumner Street and follow it up to Our Lady of the Assumption Church. Then we will proceed down Lamson Street to Maverick Street and follow it to Chelsea Street. We will continue up Chelsea Street to Brooks Street and then to Paris Street where we will stop at Sacred Heart Church. Then we will proceed down to Bennington Street and follow it up to Saratoga Street, Breed Street, and Ashley Street and to St. Joseph St. Lazarus Church. Then we will go back to Bennington Street and follow up to Walley Street and finally up Orient Ave. where we will continue to Madonna Queen National Shrine. This concludes our procession.

The exact route is as follows: It begins in front of Most Holy Redeemer Church at 72 Maverick Street. We then turn left onto Havre Street and walk one block.  From here we turn left onto Meridian Street and continue two more blocks. We again turn left until we reach Border Street. We turn left onto Border Street and continue two blocks to Maverick Street. We now turn left onto Maverick Street until we come to London Street. Turning left at this point we continue to the church parking lot located between 65 and 69 London Street. This concludes our procession.

Walkers enter the Rose Kennedy Greenway then proceed to follow along the by the harbor in the North End. Walkers then will head past the TD Garden and toward the State House. From there Walkers will head through the Boston Common, the Commonwealth Ave and then around Fenway Park.  Next, they will connect with the Emerald Necklace heading toward Jamaica Pond. Walkers enter Brookline for lunch then proceed back on the route toward West Roxbury. Walkers will travel from West Roxbury to pass through Dedham and then onto Canton.
